		<div id="comment_body_64954533"><p><div class="quote"><p>The "bad" news I keep hearing is the growing elderly are going to want labor done for them. But last I checked there's already a way to buy people's labor, you trade your own crystalized labor (money) for it. I know I'll certainly be expected to.</p></div><p>If this is intended to be serious, and not irony: no, this merely shows that you don't understand what money is or how it works on a macroeconomic level.</p><p>The fact that you can buy labor with money does not mean that labor is money. Some person still has to perform the labor.</p><p>It's like saying that, if there's a drought, no problem, I will just trade my own crystalized water (money) for it.</p></div>
