		<div id="comment_body_64954665"><p><div class="quote"><p>I suspect the competition for jobs will increase instead, because there will be fewer of them.</p></div><p>Nope. Fewer workers and proportionately fewer consumers would be a wash. What you would get would be some oversupply of factory capacity, as the output decreases,</p><p>However, what happens first is that have fewer workers but <i>not</i> fewer consumers (because old people leave the workforce but continue to consume). So you have a relative undersupply of workers, leading to decreased competition for jobs.</p></div>
